# SOW Quality Checklist

## ☐ Clarity
- [ ] No use of “TBD”, “etc.”, or vague language
- [ ] All deliverables are specific and measurable
- [ ] Scope explicitly mentions what is *out* of scope

## ☐ Structure
- [ ] All 11 key sections are present
- [ ] Sections follow logical flow
- [ ] Timeline includes milestones and dates

## ☐ Accountability
- [ ] Roles & responsibilities are clearly mapped
- [ ] No shared roles without owner

## ☐ Acceptance & Testing
- [ ] Acceptance Criteria are binary and testable
- [ ] Acceptance is linked to specific deliverables

## ☐ Assumptions & Constraints
- [ ] At least one assumption is listed
- [ ] Constraints are realistic and tied to scope

## ☐ Risk Management
- [ ] At least one project risk is documented
- [ ] Mitigation strategy is described

## ☐ Sign-off
- [ ] Signature lines or e-sign language included

## ☐ Customization
- [ ] Client-specific requirements have been translated into scope
- [ ] Template was reviewed for irrelevant sections

Run this checklist after the SOW is generated to ensure it is of high quality.
The output should be in markdown format, with same content above.

you will also add a success, failure or partial success section to the output.
